According to Chaffey and Chadwick (2016), the digital marketing strategy has many similarities to the aims of traditional marketing strategies. Some of these aims are as follows:
<br/><ul><br/><li><br/>Provide a future direction to digital marketing activities;
<br/></li><br/><li><br/>Involve analysis of the business’s external environment, internal resources and capabilities to inform strategy;
<br/></li><br/><li><br/>Define digital marketing objectives that support marketing objectives;
<br/></li><br/><li><br/>Select strategic options to achieve digital marketing objectives and create sustainable differential competitive advantage;
